g.text: You: "I haven't paid the cafeteria manager for damages yet."
Empathy: Though he finds this situation frustrating, he is doing his best to not make you feel any worse than you already do.
You: "Then I should check in with the cafeteria manager."
You: "But I don't have the money..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's talk to him anyway. An officer of the RCM shouldn't be sleeping in the streets. We'll figure something out."
Empathy: He's proud of you for getting your act together and finding a way to pay back what you owe.
You: "I think I have the money now. This is money, right?" (Show him reál bills.)
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. "I'll also take a room at the Whirling. One cannot get much closer to the crime scene."
Kim Kitsuragi: "We can pick up where we left off tomorrow morning."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You certainly have been avoiding it."
You: "I think I need to talk to the cafeteria manager about my room..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Do that. I'll be waiting for you downstairs tomorrow."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good to know. I'll be wherever is necessary in the morning. Bright and early, 7:30 sharp."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's continue tomorrow, bright and early -- 7:30 sharp. I'll be waiting downstairs."
You: "I found lodgings in the village. I'll spend the night there."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You should take care of that, then."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I'll also take a room at the Whirling."
